column4: Hello. Every time I plug in my Garmin Nuvi GPS into my Ubuntu 10.04 computer, it will crash, show a black screen with a frozen mouse, and the Capslock and Scroll Lock keyboard lights will blink. Anyone know what might be causing this?
does the nuvi have a differential serial interface or just USB?
only usb
can you check your dmesg logs?
how would I do this?
in /var/log, find the dmesg log that has a created date closest to before your machine crashed (probably just dmesg, could be dmesg.1.gz)
ok, I have it. Now what?
ok, I have the log. Now what?
are you back?
you on?
kinda
ok, please don't stay just because of me. What do I do with the logs now?
look at them
Ok, I'll try to find that
the time stamp never resets back to 0. Once it starts going up, it keeps going up. What would the assigning line look like?
it'll be before it started going up
should I pastebin the files? I can't seem to find anything. You would probably be much better at this
i'm about to go out the door
ok. Well, thanks anyways :D
ok. I will
